      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Bridge Design Pattern :- Inheritance is bad use composition, while extending the classes  both parent and child",
      "fontSize": 28,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Bridge Design Pattern :- Inheritance is bad use composition, while extending the classes  both parent and child",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2M6C60sJlzqTDR37qGUDC",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 256.7259216308594,
      "y": 208.29998779296875,
      "width": 1389.35888671875,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a4",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1422451722,
      "version": 189,
      "versionNonce": 1874513482,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776849114949,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Split a large clas into saparate hierarchies (abstraction and implementation) which can be developed independently - strucutural design pattern",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Split a large clas into saparate hierarchies (abstraction and implementation) which can be developed independently - strucutural design pattern",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "DjV7Nmgp1dYXdZ7cnPXKi",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 222.72592163085938,
      "y": 317.29998779296875,
      "width": 1386.539306640625,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "a8",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1466361994,
      "version": 580,
      "versionNonce": 1873331350,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776852823128,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When we have mulltiple future needs of parent and child clasess like, car and engine, multiple cars like sedan, hatchback, suv, while \nengine etc petro, diesel, electric etc all, each can be paired with any like suv elevtric,.. so we dont have to create like classes like \nSuvWithDieselEngine, or HatchbackWithPetrol.. aise toh bht saari choices hogi with each other right to fix this simplle we need to use is the \nbridge pattern ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When we have mulltiple future needs of parent and child clasess like, car and engine, multiple cars like sedan, hatchback, suv, while \nengine etc petro, diesel, electric etc all, each can be paired with any like suv elevtric,.. so we dont have to create like classes like \nSuvWithDieselEngine, or HatchbackWithPetrol.. aise toh bht saari choices hogi with each other right to fix this simplle we need to use is the \nbridge pattern ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
