    {
      "id": "cC7K9GCpxz_io47pKoZoF",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 405.7259216308594,
      "y": 2265.2999877929688,
      "width": 924.9993286132812,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0p",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 616104586,
      "version": 104,
      "versionNonce": 575023562,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776855612465,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Bridge Decouples an abstraction from its implementation, so that both can vary independently.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Bridge Decouples an abstraction from its implementation, so that both can vary independently.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Ie7LkYXzl0oZsHT8fGcAh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 346.7259216308594,
      "y": 2344.2999877929688,
      "width": 1459.0189208984375,
      "height": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0r",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1253966230,
      "version": 558,
      "versionNonce": 498523594,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776855833607,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Stratrgy vs Bridge :- Here the abstraction is like client in strategy and implpementation is like each strategy it makes it similar\nAll the Design Pattern -> clean code, Tighttly Couples to lossesly couple\nthe diffrence is here of intent, like strategy is for client can use multiple algorithm using interchanbly dynamically change the strategy during runtime \nStrategy is like dono interchanbly use kar paying in the client code thats why diffrent strategy ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Stratrgy vs Bridge :- Here the abstraction is like client in strategy and implpementation is like each strategy it makes it similar\nAll the Design Pattern -> clean code, Tighttly Couples to lossesly couple\nthe diffrence is here of intent, like strategy is for client can use multiple algorithm using interchanbly dynamically change the strategy during runtime \nStrategy is like dono interchanbly use kar paying in the client code thats why diffrent strategy ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "OPexs9gNU_DrmYw3ojfyS",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 346.7259216308594,
      "y": 2457.2999877929688,
      "width": 953.619384765625,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
